description:
If you did not think that we will do a page-by-page analysis of "Grover's Eight Nights of Light", then you don't know Jew or Not Jew!






cur = 0;
tx = document.getElementById("txt");
pc = document.getElementById("pic");
but = document.ff.btn;
text = new Array(
tx.innerHTML,
"Right out of a gate, a very nice touch. You see that Hooper's Store sign? That's a reference to the obviously Jewish Mr. Hooper. But why is Big Bird carrying a menorah? He is clearly goyishe.",
"The goyishe couple Ernie and Bert are not carrying any Jewish paraphernalia. Cookie Monster is obviously carrying cookies. Why, Big Bird? Why?",
"Now, we're here to determine if Grover is actually Jewish, or just celebrates Hanukkah so that Sesame Street can be inclusive... you know, like the Winnie-the-Pooh and the Hanukkah Dreidel, or Porky the Pig's Purim.",
"This woman is Jewish. I think this pretty much settles it. Does Grover have a dad? How would this impact his I Score?",
"Now, Elmo is clearly goyishe. We sure hope Grover can teach him and Abby the true meaning of Hanukkah! (Not the true story, which better goes unsaid: Massacre. Lots and lots of massacre.)",
"That's a wig, right? Is Grover's mother Orthodox?",
"This is the last page Amazon made available in its free preview, and we're not paying $3.49 for the paperback version. Still, feel free to do so and let us know what happens next!",
"That Big Bird menorah still bothers us. Perhaps he bought at a local Judaica store as a gift for a Jewish friend?",
);
ln = text.length;
function next() {
 cur++;
 txt.innerHTML = text[cur];
 pc.src = 'img/other/grover/grover'+(cur+1)+'.jpg';
 if (cur == ln-1) {
  cur = -1;
  but.value = 'Restart';
 } else if (cur == 0) {
  but.value = 'Next';
 }
}
